This is a Python script that takes an OpenType font and activates a
given feature so that it can be used in non OpenType savvy applications,
it can even be use to always turn a feature on.

Only single substitution features are supported.

It requires FontForge with Python scripting support.


Usage: deotfy.py OPTION... FILE...

Options:
  -o, --output=FILE         file name of the resulting font
  -f, --feature=FEATURE     OpenType feature tag to be activated
  -s, --script=SCRIPT       optional OpenType script tag
  -l, --language=LANGUAGE   optional OpenType language tag

  -h, --help                print this message and exit
  -v, --verbose             verbose mode

